\series bold
\color blue

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Solution
\series default
\color inherit
: We know from the lecture slides that the conjugate prior is 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta\sim\mathrm{Gamma}(\alpha,\beta)$
\end_inset

 giving the posterior 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta\vert x_{1},...,x_{4}\sim\mathrm{Gamma}(\alpha+\sum_{i=1}^{4}x_{i},\beta+n)$
\end_inset

, and the data is: 
\begin_inset Formula $n=4$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{i=1}^{4}x_{i}=946.$
\end_inset

 We need to determine 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

 in the prior.
 From the properties of the Gamma distribution
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
E(\theta) & =\frac{\alpha}{\beta}=250\\
Var(\theta) & =\frac{\alpha}{\beta^{2}}=50^{2}.
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Now, solving this system of equation gives 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=25$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta=0.1$
\end_inset

.
 The posterior is therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta\vert x_{1},...,x_{4}\sim\mathrm{Gamma}(971,4.1).$
\end_inset

